summary: An ordinance accepting an easement for a right of way for street purposes across Tracts 5 to 8 inclusive and Tracts 17 to 20 inclusive of the Subdivision of Section 10, Township 25 North, Range 4 East, W. M., granted the City of Seattle by the Department of Public Lands of the State of Washington, April 10, 1928; and laying off 43rd Avenue Northeast.
